data.enText: not good or not as good as sb/sth else

data.chText: 现代音乐常被认为不如过去的。
data.enText: Modern music is often considered inferior to that of the past.

data.chText: 不如别人的人；级别（或地位）低的人
data.enText: a person who is not as good as sb else; a person who is lower in rank or status

simple_means.memory_skill: infer 下面 + ior 较…的，属于…的 → 低下的，下等的

tr: a character or symbol set or printed or written beneath or slightly below and to the side of another character
one of lesser rank or station or quality
falling short of some prescribed norm
of or characteristic of low rank or importance
having an orbit between the sun and the Earth's orbit
example: Mercury and Venus are inferior planets

tr: written or printed below and to one side of another character
lower than a given reference point

value.def: Something that is inferior is not as good as something else.

example.ex: The cassettes were of inferior quality...
This resulted in overpriced and often inferior products...
example.tran: 这就导致了标价过高而往往质量低劣的产品的出现。

example.ex: If children were made to feel inferior to other children their confidence declined.
example.tran: 如果让孩子感觉他们不如其他孩子,他们的信心就会减弱。

value.def: If one person is regarded as inferior to another, they are regarded as less important because they have less status or ability.

example.ex: He preferred the company of those who were intellectually inferior to himself.
example.tran: 他喜欢与那些智力水平不如他的人共处。

example.ex: ...the inferior status of women in pre-revolutionary Russia...
example.tran: 革命之前俄国妇女的低微地位

example.ex: Most career women make me feel inferior.
example.tran: 大部分职业女性让我感到自己不如她们。

example.ex: A gentleman should always be civil, even to his inferiors.
example.tran: 绅士应该总是彬彬有礼,即便是对地位不及自己者。

value.tran: (地位、能力等)低等的,低于…的;下级的

example.ex: I found it difficult to shake off a sense of social inferiority.
example.tran: 我发现很难摆脱社交自卑感。

partsOfSpeech.dec: anter〔= ante前面〕+ ior 较…的，属于…的 → 较早的
exter 外 + ior 较…的，属于…的 → 外部的
infer 下面 + ior 较…的，属于…的 → 低下的，下等的
inter 内 + ior 较…的，属于…的 → 内部的
post 后 + er + ior 较…的，属于…的 → 较后的
sen 年老 + ior 人 → 年长者
super 上 + ior 人 → 上级
warr〔= war战争〕+ ior 人 → 勇士，斗士
